cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with learning unsupervised representations of images that are invariant to confounding factors. This is a problem that is commonly encountered in computer vision, and hence, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in deep learning, and hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses deep convolutional autoencoders, which are a type of neural network, and hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with microscopy imaging, which is a type of medical imaging, and hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category.
